{"id":14880710,"mediaExerciseId":"7d83df32-b352-44be-8eea-1f3c93a3ce2a","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"1","chapterTitle":"Introduction To Corporate Finance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"1.3","sectionTitle":"The Goal of Financial Management","pageNumber":10,"solutions":[{"id":5875433,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine the goal of financial management, the shortcomings of the goal of profit maximization, and define corporate finance.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":97,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/02e26dfdffec362d3676f50b7e5a7924/lateximg_large.png","width":1023},"regular":{"height":50,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/02e26dfdffec362d3676f50b7e5a7924/lateximg.png","width":512}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financial management.\n\n**Financial management** is a strategic planning, organizing, directing, and controlling of a company's finances.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/565f4ef44059beaabc55bbe8267c8c36/lateximg_large.png","width":993},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/565f4ef44059beaabc55bbe8267c8c36/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"a. The goal of financial management is to maximize shareholders' wealth.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/803d948ba5bca2eca9a9cf79d82527f4/lateximg_large.png","width":974},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/803d948ba5bca2eca9a9cf79d82527f4/lateximg.png","width":487}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"b. Some shortcomings of the goal of profit maximization are ignoring the intangible benefits and the welfare of stakeholders of the company, taking advantage of the vendors or employees and producing goods of poor quality. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/0f327ca3585c856e912a9ead6b97a97f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/0f327ca3585c856e912a9ead6b97a97f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"c. **Corporate finance** is an area in finance that deals with sources of funding, capital structuring, and investment decisions.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/89ea41bef2eca4db565db7cd44c42f03/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/13/663114b2752e338fc3cb78e31329a96c/89ea41bef2eca4db565db7cd44c42f03/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"0f6fa0e8-4df6-444f-a5c3-1ab387ea3f13","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5},{"id":5981890,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 1\n\nIn this question, we are asked the goal of financial management.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Let us define first **financial management**, this is the strategic way of planning how an organization earn or spend their resources. \n\nThe aim of financial management is to maximize the wealth of shareholders by increasing the current value per share of the existing stock. A good financial decision will increase the value of the stock while a bad financial decision do otherwise.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":213,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c224dbfbfacc06b365640fe925220814/216a2c9aca3bfc4e565fa14f010fb5cd/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":108,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c224dbfbfacc06b365640fe925220814/216a2c9aca3bfc4e565fa14f010fb5cd/lateximg.png","width":500}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 2\n\nIn this question, we are asked what is lacking in the goal of profit maximization.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The shortcoming of the goal of profit maximization is the ambiguity of the criterion and the vagueness of time period. It does not state whether to maximize the profit in the long-run or short-run. Profit maximization is not a precise objective since it does not consider risk. \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c224dbfbfacc06b365640fe925220814/f2c5cbd0baf1916b824ad73ad00821a5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c224dbfbfacc06b365640fe925220814/f2c5cbd0baf1916b824ad73ad00821a5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 3\n\nIn this question, we are asked to define corporate finance. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**Corporate Finance** is a specific area wherein corporations analyze their financial decisions they about to make such as investment, financing, dividend and daily operations.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c224dbfbfacc06b365640fe925220814/883e7b3de64ccd7a33082185d83e44a8/lateximg_large.png","width":1004},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c224dbfbfacc06b365640fe925220814/883e7b3de64ccd7a33082185d83e44a8/lateximg.png","width":501}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"b522393a-9647-46a5-a1ef-da00ab381d41","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880712,"exerciseName":"1","page":12,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1747f128-86ee-4c45-8415-f3a12a37f0e3","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-1-exercises-1-1747f128-86ee-4c45-8415-f3a12a37f0e3"},{"id":14880713,"exerciseName":"2","page":12,"hasSolution"